# AI Agent Operations & Git Safety

You are assisting with the development of a production website. Because multiple developers and AI agents are working on this repository simultaneously, you MUST adhere to the following Git safety rules before executing any code changes.

## 🚨 CRITICAL GIT WORKFLOW 🚨

1. **ALWAYS PULL FIRST:** Before you analyze files, plan changes, or write any code, you MUST execute `git pull origin main` (or the respective branch) to ensure you have the latest changes. Do not assume your local environment is up to date.
2. **USE FEATURE BRANCHES:** If the task requires more than a simple typo fix, create a new branch (`git checkout -b feature/name-of-feature`) instead of working directly on `main`.
3. **DO NOT OVERWRITE BLINDLY:** If a `git push` fails due to the remote containing work that you do not have locally (e.g., another developer pushed changes while you were working), **DO NOT FORCE PUSH (`git push -f`)**. 
4. **RESOLVE CONFLICTS:** If there is a merge conflict or a push rejection, pull the latest changes, resolve the conflicts safely, and ask the user to verify before proceeding.
5. **COMMIT FREQUENTLY:** Make logical, atomic commits with clear messages so work is easily tracked and revertible.

By strictly following these rules, you will prevent overriding the work of Alexander or any other team member on the repository.
